5: Oh dear. Are you all right, Alk?
9: More or less... Closer to less, really.
19:
Pray wait, Lady Stella! To do so
would invite great danger. Why, look
at how Alk writhes in pain on the
sand, helpless like a wounded rabbit!
24:
Haha! You know, you're hard to read,
Mr. Prince! I haven't figured out if
you're an overconfident buffoon or a
faint-hearted dandy!
28:
But anyway, we'll have more than
enough time for jet skiing later!
Marina's already off doing
something else!
32:
Okay, Mia, race you to that cliff over
there! Let's go!
36:
Huh?!
That came out of nowhere... but
there's no way I'm turning down a
challenge like that! You're on!
40:
Oh my, Marina hasn't changed a
bit.
Ah yes, there's nothing more
BEAUTIFUL than staying true to
oneself!
44:
Huh, you and Marina know each
other? That's news to me.
48:
Indeed! I can scarce remember how
long ago it was, but tales of her
BEAUTY made their way to me, of
course!
50:
Though is there really anyone in the
whole wide ocean who hasn't heard
the name of the Crimson Blades? I
think not!
54:
Oh yeah, they're a household name
by now. Marina too. Not to brag, but I
actually knew her before she was
famous, you know!
56:
She saved me when I got captured
and sold to pirates! I was fifteen
back then, so... that was about four
years ago, I guess!
61: I'm sorry, you were WHAT now?
65:
She's in such high spirits now
though! I gotta admit, I was a little
worried when she asked me to get a
ship ready all urgent-like.
69:
I heard that this island is also a
high-class resort.
72:
Yep. They call it Paradise Isle. It's
actually entirely artificial—some big
shots figured they'd make a whole
new island.
76:
Marina mentioned she wanted to
find the buyer of that rare treasure...
Though I haven't the foggiest what
she plans to do with it!
80:
I'm sure she'll tell us her reasons
when the time comes. In the
meantime, all we can do is enjoy
ourselves to our heart's content!
84:
Now that is a positively BEAUTIFUL
idea!
89:
Aren't we missing someone?
Where's Light?
92:
Ah, the great champion is currently
off with that GORGEOUS knight and
his little princess companion.
96: How are you holding up, Gerard?
100:
I must admit, I do have the slightest
cramp in my neck...
106:
Oh, so I'm a pain in the neck, huh? Is
that what you're trying to say?
108:
How rude! Aren't you supposed to
be a chivalrous knight or whatever?
111:
I beg your forgiveness, my lady! It's
just that... a knight is usually one
who rides, not who is ridden!
116:
But your helmet makes you look just
like a horse! Maybe if you started
neighing it might help you get into
the mood?
120:
Not the helm! Anything but the helm,
I beg you not to lay hands on it!
125:
Dinah? Where are you running off
to?! Come back!
137:
Rouse yourself, young lad! Can you
hear the sound of my voice?
145:
Thankfully, his pulse and breathing
seem to be in order. Let's move him
somewhere safe.
160:
Haha! Now things are starting to get
interesting.
